A month ago, Bart wrote:
> The other problem is that when I answer "y" to the question "there are
> insecure directories -- proceed?" I expected that to mean that it
> would USE those directories, not ignore them.  If it's going to skip
> those directories anyway, why bother to ask the question?  Giving me a
> choice between no directories and half of them is no choice at all; it
> just leaves me with a partly-working completion system, which is
> baffling.

Nothing seems to have been done about this.  Also, it would be nice if
the user gets told which directories are insecure, otherwise he
doesn't stand much of a chance of fixing them.

Maybe I should file a SF bug report?

